General Motors Corp. 's Chevrolet division said in Detroit that it is offering owners of imported vehicles a $1,400 rebate toward the purchase or lease of any 1990 Geo Prizm model.
Owners of domestically made vehicles will receive an $800 rebate.
Geo Prizm prices start at $10,125. 

Customers can choose finance rates ranging from 6.9% to 10.9% instead of the rebate.
The rebates and low-rate financing are available "until further notice," Chevrolet said. 

Chevrolet had a 125-day supply of Prizm cars at the end of September, according to Ward's Automotive Reports, an industry statistical publication.
A 60-day to 65-day supply is considered normal. 

